Content Selection - Single Selection Mode
Content Selection - Multiple Selection Mode
Preview button acts as a toggle.
Floating back/forward buttons allow browsing through content items. Browsing order follows what is visible in the content grid.
Vertical scrolling allows browsing within multi-page documents.
When multiple content items are being selected, preview does not allow browsing between or within multipage documents. Selection can be toggled by clicking the content items.
Uses a select then act workflow, which allows content to be selected without being forced through a preview step.
Has a number of implications for the design of Files: 1. Requires the use of an action bar. 2. Obsoletes the need for selection mode.
When multiple content items are being selected, preview does not allow browsing.

Multiple Selection Mode
Preview button acts as a toggle.
Floating back/forward buttons allow browsing through content. Browsing order follows what is visible in the content grid.
The selection moves with as you browse, so that the visible content item is always selected.
When multiple content items are being selected, preview does not allow browsing. Selection can be toggled by clicking the content items.
